Beautiful People!  One of my favorite things to do is volunteer in my community.  To help me get started on the process, I headed over to servevirginia.org/quiz

@serve_virginia is the perfect resource to inspire us to volunteer in our community.  The great thing is that it doesn’t matter if this is your first time volunteering, or if volunteering has become part of your lifestyle.  Serve Virginia is here to help guide you to find opportunities that complements you best.

Once I took the quiz to find out my “Volunteer Personality”, and let me just say, this was so much fun to do, the next step was to find out the results.  Well, it’s no surprise that my results were helping kids.

I love to encourage kids to read, so I utilized @handsonrva to find service opportunities near me and decided to donate a few children’s books to the @littlefreelibrary in my area.  Knowing that the kids who are going to select the books that I donated, will put a smile on their faces and be an inspiration to them is such a wonderful feeling.  I encourage you all to volunteer and a great place to start the process is by visiting servevirginia.org/quiz

Happy Volunteering Y’all!
